@baseUrl = http://localhost:8888
@token = paste-login-token-here

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health

### Swagger OpenAPI JSON
GET {{baseUrl}}/v3/api-docs

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "flowdesk-local-owner",
  "password": "local-only-bootstrap-password"
}

### Current demo user info
# Replace the id with a real user id returned by login or user list.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/user/example-user-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### User list
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/user/list?page=1&count=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Upload a safe local sample file
# Replace the file path with a synthetic public-safe file.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/upload/file
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=flowdesk-demo

--flowdesk-demo
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

This is a public-safe synthetic demo document for Flowdesk.
--flowdesk-demo--

### AI chat
# Works with FLOWDESK_AI_PROVIDER=ollama or dashscope when FLOWDESK_AI_ENABLED=true.
# With AI disabled, the response contains a clear disabled message.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompts": "Create a short todo list for preparing a public GitHub release.",
  "chatType": 0,
  "relationId": "local-demo"
}

### Knowledge status, dev profile only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/diag/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Knowledge search, dev profile only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/diag/search?query=public%20release
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
